sql:
SELECT facility_name, capacity
FROM facility_details
WHERE location IS NOT NULL;

SELECT AVG(traffic_volume / travel_time) AS average_traffic_flow
FROM traffic_analytics
WHERE facility_id = (SELECT facility_id FROM facility_details WHERE facility_name = 'Main Street');

external_knowledge:
Facility capacity refers to the maximum number of vehicles a facility can handle; 
The cav_percentage represents the proportion of self-driving or highly automated vehicles in the traffic flow; 
The intervehicle_gap is a measure of the average distance between vehicles in the traffic.

sql:
SELECT MAX(base_capacity) AS max_capacity
FROM traffic_parameters
WHERE facility_type = 'Freeway';

SELECT cav_percentage
FROM traffic_parameters
WHERE facility_type = 'Freeway';

SELECT COUNT(vehicle_id) 
FROM platoon_vehicles 
WHERE position = 1;
